  "prompt": "How wax KVPY SX stream exam?",
  "response": "The Kishore Vaigyanik Protsahan Yojana (KVPY) SX stream exam is designed for students enrolled in the 12th grade (Science stream). The exam is intended to identify and nurture talented students who are interested in pursuing research careers in the field of basic sciences.\n\nHere are some key points about the KVPY SX stream exam:\n\n1. **Eligibility**: Students enrolled in Class 12 with a minimum of 75% (65% for SC/ST/PWD) in math and science subjects in Class 10 board exams.\n\n2. **Exam Pattern**:\n   - **Part I**: Consists of multiple-choice questions from four subjects: Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, and Biology. Students are required to attempt any three out of four subjects.\n   - **Part II**: Also consists of multiple-choice questions from the same four subjects, but students need to attempt any two out of four subjects.\n\n3. **Syllabus**: The syllabus for the SX stream includes topics from Class XI and XII for Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, and Biology.\n\n4. **Duration**: The exam is usually conducted for a duration of three hours.\n\n5. **Marking Scheme**: Typically, there is a negative marking for incorrect answers in both Part I and Part II.\n\n6. **Preparation**: Students are advised to thoroughly study their Class XI and XII NCERT textbooks and practice previous years' question papers. Regular practice and understanding of fundamental concepts are crucial for scoring well.\n\n7. **Selection Process**: Based on the performance in the aptitude test, short-listed candidates are called for an interview. The final selection is based on the combined performance in the aptitude test and the interview.\n\n8. **Benefits**: Selected students receive a fellowship and contingency grants up to the pre-Ph.D. level. They also get opportunities to attend summer programs and interact with leading scientists.\n\nTo perform well in the KVPY SX stream exam, it is important to have a strong grasp of the concepts, practice regularly, and manage time effectively during the exam.",
